reviews.review_text: i really cant figure out..... ...why they have never had an official release of full sets of the dylan/dead soundboards. Is this the only one in existence or somethin? They gotta have em in the vault somewhere. These shows are to important to let it vanish into the cluttered closet of history. When they released View from the Vault 4, for some reason both dylan/dead sets were not there. The one compilation that is available has only a few songs and is barley a glimpse of what went on at these shows. Is it somthin with Dylan not wantin to release it? if anyone knows ide be interested to hear why these havent seen the light of day in sbd. as for this sbd, i was really excited to see it actually existed and highly reccomend this show, especially set 3 of course. you wont be disapointed, the quality of the 3rd set is also really good, the auds are OK. love the archive, thanks to the people involved in getting this up.
Solid Gold 3rd Set Wonderful SBD for the 3rd set w/ Dylan.  Gracias, Painoman.
just the first 2 great late 80s show, nice let it grow, love opening with iko and a solid second set, execution and selection wise

One of the most Awesome Sets I know of There is something unique, magical and cherished about this particular presentation of the Dylan /Dead set. I keep coming back to it, amazed and humbled by the way everyone here is pretty much in unison and at the top of their game. I don't claim to be an expert on here. Heck, this is my first review. I tend to travel around the Dead shows on Archive and Sugarmegs looking for great versions of their ballads, which I know are naussiating to some out there. The rhythmic and melodious magic that comes off of Jerry's strings is irreplaceable and mesmerizing when he is on and one with his machine. I close my eyes when I listen to Frankie Lee and Judas Priest, then into Stuck Inside of Memphis, and I visualize the band and Dylan coalescing in near perfect vision of where they are, what they're playing, and what each of them gathered along the long, strange trip to bring to the show this particular evening. I wonder if I'm ADD the way I keep coming back to this show. I've listened to other shows from this tour and they pale by comparison. And I would love nothing better than to be pointed in the direction of ANY show that comes near this one with Dylan. The Peggy-O seems pretty lackluster to me, another one of my faves. Oh, what a blessing to be able to tune in here every day and get a lot or a little of Jerry and his guitar work to make my day better!

excellent The Grateful Dead and Bob Dylan sets were getting tighter each show, I could listen to this show again and again, The Dylan set is so especially great. Yes, Yes, Yes, The Grateful Dead and Bob Dylan @ Autzen Stadium in beautiful Eugene, Oregon (a relaxing place for epic concerts). I enjoy each and every unique show, so 5 stars (again.

My first show! Can't believe I was 15 years old! This day and all the memories that surround it will be long held. So many dear friends and family. Still remember exactly where we were on the floor at Autzen. Those were the days...
